The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Big day for me: Jhulan
                                                                                                                       7                                      Big day for me: Jhulan
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                      
	New Delhi: For Jhulan Goswami, the Arjuna Award is something unique.         
	This award will help me become a more matured person, said the woman cricketer minutes after she was conferred with the Arjuna by President Pratibha Patil on Sunday.         
	My responsibilities have increased now. As a senior cricketer, I should be able to contribute more to the game. Its a big day for me, said the India bcaptain.         
	Jhulan said she enjoyed her journey as a cricketer.         
	Deepak Mondal said the Indian football was moving in the right direction. Under Bob Houghton, the national team is doing extremely well. I am sure many more footballers will win Arjuna from the next year.                                                                                                                     
